learning_outcomes:
In this session, we will explore:

Your role as a supervisor to have purposeful conversations with officers that spark motivation and bring clarity to development paths;
Practical frameworks to support better career conversations;
Navigating common career challenges and strategies to overcome them

Analyse key regulatory processes by mapping the journey of stakeholders to assess points of inefficiency and efficiency;
Apply the 5 regulatory review guiding principles and design considerations in reviewing their agency’s regulatory requirements; and
Develop a “Case for Change” to recommend actionable improvements to regulatory design and delivery.

Demonstrate shared ownership of national priorities and Public Service outcomes;
Develop their capability to lead self and influence others within a complex system;
Build diverse partnerships and expand networks for inclusive policymaking and to deliver effectively on national challenges;
Cultivate and sustain a leadership community for effective Whole-Of-Government (WOG) collaboration; and
Model the core values of the Public Service and cultivate a values-based culture within their departments.

To equip participants with the knowledge and skills to conduct red-teaming, and to lead teams to do red-teaming in their agencies.




Participants will be able to:

•	Learn how to analyse issues of concern;

•	Identify potential public reactions and counter-narratives; 

•	Propose possible communications interventions.

Develop a broader perspective of Public Service priorities, so as to purposefully contribute through their work;
Develop personal leadership practices such as self-reflection, effective interpersonal communication, and continuous learning, to navigate work complexities and challenges; and  
Build a collaborative community that enables mutual learning and support

The ELP is designed to support learners in: 

Developing strategies to lead in response to key shifts in our operating context;
Growing the ability to drive and sustain innovation and transformation; 
Building a leadership community for professional and emotional support, as well as effective Whole-of-Government collaboration; and 
Evaluating how they lead by example, as well as inspire trust and a sense of purpose in their teams.
